                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#141r">Fols. 141r-142</locus>r: Märgämä kǝbr "Refutation of the Glory", a didactic poem. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           A didactic poem in Old Amharic, most probably incomplete, possibly a fragment of a different manuscript. The text is written in a late 17th-/early 18th-cent. hand (similar, but not identical to the main hand of the Ms.). 
The title of the poem appears in the upper margin. The poem shows striking similarity, in both the content and style, to "an archaic Amharic poem" published by Getatchew Haile ("An Archaic Amharic Poem on Condemning Wealth and Glory", in: G.Khan, Semitic Studies in Honour of Edward Ullendorff, Leiden - Boston 2005, 255-75); still, this "Refutation of the Glory" is a different text.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#143ra">Fol. 143ra-143</locus>vb: Prayer over the blessed bread (eulogia), two prayers after meals.  <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The prayers are probably connected with the consuming of the eulogia by celebrant clergy at the end of Mass.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#149v">Fols. 149v-149</locus>r-145v: Mästäbqwǝˤat "Supplications". <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#145v">Fol. 145v</locus>: Prayer before the liturgical reading from the Gospel (cp. MQ I, ch. 3, 186).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           This text is absent from its proper place in fol. 23rb. In fol. 145v it is written in a different hand.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#151r">Fols. 151r-151</locus>v-150r-150v: Prayers before the reading from the Miracles of Mary (cp. fol. 151vb).  <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in two different hands, in the reversed direction.
                        </item>
                     </list>
